  m_Name: Pes_Middle_Phalanx_D5_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Middle_Phalanx_D5_L
  partName: Pes Middle Phalanx D5 Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left middle phalanx of the fifth hind digit is positioned between the proximal
    and distal phalanges within the canine hindpaw. This structure supports flexibility,
    toe stability, and coordinated movement during locomotion and weight-bearing
    activities. Tendons and ligaments associated with the phalanx enable controlled
    digital flexion and extension
  - while maintaining balanced paw mechanics. The fifth digit contributes to traction,
    maneuverability, and distribution of mechanical forces across the hindpaw. Proper
    alignment and structural health are essential for efficient movement and stable
    gait patterns.
